review_blob: Im really starting to appreciate how bad these typical "American lager" beers really are. Urine color and poor scent. Smoothish drink but terrible aftertaste. Really just a bad, bad beer.

Pretty copper brown color with a surprisingly sweet hoppy aroma. As I write this Im excited to dig in. Super smooth and clean finish. Classic IPA, but with a little extra sweetness and clarity. Its a great beer, but it only gets a 3.3 because none of the characteristics were extraordinary. But  I must clarify, as a whole it was very tasty!

Pretty brown bronze color with a nice roasted scent. Unfortunately, the taste didnt stand up to the smell and look of the beer. Smooth, but not really much of a flavor. Taste was just pale and light. Not bad, but just didnt stand up to what I had expected...Definitely a decent beer, but nothing special

Holy cow...First off this beer is black, not dark brown, but black with a beautiful chocolate brown head and nice roasty aroma. Had a sip...Oh yes! Yummy coffee roast flavor that leaves a slight tingle on my tongue. This is the type of beer Ive been looking for! Delicious!
Pretty red brown flavor with a nice head to it. Standard IPA aroma but with a little added kick to it. Very bitter, caught me a little off guard, but again a pretty standard finish. Good, not great.
Cheap smell and color. Ive had this several times but decided to rate it this time....Not particularly smooth for a cheap beer, all around just bad.

Pretty maple brown color with a slight hopsy scent. Had a little bit of a kick to it, but nice mild hops with a somewhat harsh finish. I definitely liked liked it, something different than what Ive been having lately.
Nice chestnut color with an overall very average aroma. Lots of beading! Smooth drink, a tasty ale, but nothing too different.

Nice dark pour with a little bit of brown. I felt the taste was bland. Nothing to flavorful, slightly smooth for a 9% beer, but not any real flavor either. For my first corked beer, it wasnt anything great.
Pretty orange color with a little bit of rust. Standard IPA aroma. Hoppy taste, but nothing special. I like IPAs, but this still a "meh" for me.

beer_brewer_name: Leinenkugel Brewing Company (Tenth & Blake Beer Co.)
review_blob: Very very dark, almost black, but still had a hint of brown. I could smell a slight bit of scotch, but it definitely wasnt too much, and still had the ale scent I expected. I was expecting the "scotch" to be stronger in the taste, and at 9.5% I definitely wasnt expecting something quite so smooth. Nice mild vanilla aftertaste. I would definitely recommend this one!
beer_name: Leinenkugels Big Eddy Wee Heavy Scotch Ale

review_blob: The scent reminded me very much of a sour apple jolly rancher. Pretty root beer color pout, the picture above is much darker than my pour. Flavor had a little bit of the apple as well. Overall a decent beer, but nothing to get too excited over.

For me, this is a classic Chicago beer that is really enjoyable. Nice golden pour that sticks all over the inside of the glass. Great IPA taste and smooth finish. Definitely a go to beer here in Chicago, nothing too special, but at the same time, a consistently refreshing taste.

Poured a very pretty orange gold color with very little head. Smell and taste was exactly like that of a barn...It could have been liquid straw and I wouldnt have known any better. That being said, it was so unique and surprising, I liked it a lot. Not something to drink over and over, but once in a while it will definitely spice things up.
A nice dark gold color, with a very smooth finish. You can definitely taste the hops, and definitely a beer worth having again.

I drank this beer again in the interest of rating it. Now that Im taking in the smell and look its more disappointing than I realized. Normal golden pour, but it smells like dirt. Taste wasnt much better either, nothing worth seeking out. "When I drink beer, I definitely dont prefer Dos Equis"

Poured a yellow gold, but much more opaque than the usual lager color.... I was interested. I could taste some lemon, but at the same time it had a subtle sweet taste. A sure winner, definitely would have another!
For a summer beer, I must say it was just like every other one Ive had. Notes of lemon, and the usual pale yellow color. Not that its a bad beer, just nothing new or special.
Wow, what a pretty looking beer. Not much of a head, but a nice maple color.    For lack of a better word, it had a woody taste. Smooth finish, and definitely a beer I would have again
beer_name: Samuel Adams Imperial Series Double Bock

review_blob: I was excited for this one, as it was something I considered a classic IPA. Poured a beautiful golden color and gave that hopsy smell I love. Had a sip, wasnt disappointed, but not blow off my feet either. A good IPA, but nothing to go wild over. A smooth drink, that I would buy again, but not get too excited about.

I poured this beer and got a nice dark and clean pour and was very excited. As someone who likes porters, I was extremely excited do dig in, but unfortunately, the flavor didnt really resemble "oatmeal" to me, but instead tasted very unoriginal. Not a bad beer, but not the new different taste I was hoping for.

Poured nice and was looking and smelling good to start. Unfortunately, this isnt really my style of beer as reflected in my rating. I can see the appreciation for it, but for me it just wasnt a huge hit.
UPDATED: JUL 16, 2012

Poured the beer and loved the aroma and look, so I was very excited to have a taste. It was very strong, and lacked the "IPA" taste I was expecting, leaving me slightly disappointed, but I can see how it would be appealing to someone who appreciated bold taste.
